\h2{What is shttpd?}
\tt{echo-httpd}, \tt{redir-httpd}, and \tt{cgi-httpd} are HTTP
daemons designed to complement publicfile.

\tt{echo-httpd} echos HTTP requests.

\tt{echo-config} configures \tt{echo-httpd}.

\tt{redir-httpd} redirects HTTP requests via cdb lookup.

\tt{redir-config} configures \tt{redir-httpd}.

\tt{cgi-httpd} and \tt{cgiuser-httpd} execute a cgi script.

\tt{cgi-config} and \tt{cgiuser-config} configure \tt{cgi-httpd} and
\tt{cgiuser-httpd}, respectively.

\tt{cgi-dispatch} executes a CGI program specified by the environment variable
\tt{PATH_INFO}.

\tt{constant-httpd} prints the same file for each HTTP request.

\tt{constant-config} configures \tt{constant-httpd}.

Each instance of an shttpd daemon listens on a separate address, in a
\tt{chroot} directory (except for \tt{cgiuser-httpd}), typically running as a
nonprivileged user.

\h2{Related Software}
